HELENS SPIRIT stalked off rail, finished well outside. PAYITFORWARD bumped at the break with FREEDOM CONVOY, advanced inside, well placed back of bid battle turn, tired stretch. JACKIE'S THUNDER stalked wide, faded. FREEDOM CONVOY, bumped at the break, opened up, took inside, pressured turn, gave way late turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: J. W. Sifton S. ASSINIBOIA DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 78. Stakes Purse 40250. 3-YEAR-OLDS. Manitoba and Saskatchewan Foals. Colts and Geldings. Weight 122 lbs. Fees: $240 to enter - $240 to start. Non-nominated horses can be made eligible by paying 1% of purse plus missed nominations by May 16 to the CTHS Office or 10% of purse at time of entry to the race office plus enter and start fees. Nominations Closed.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUGAR DADDY JACK stalked inside, back of bid battle final turn, rallied outside, drew even with I LOVE MY LIFE passing sixteenth pole, drew out late. VALID DEFENCE trailed to stretch, finished well outside to take the place. I LOVE MY LIFE bobbled at the break, pressed outside, forced issue three-wide after a half, dueled outside final turn, gradually shook PRIVATE FRANK to his inside by mid stretch, couldn't hold off the ralliers late. KENTUCKY JAKE stalked off rail, ralied belatedly. KEYSTONE CASH opened up early, took inside, pressured after half, gave way into final turn. PRIVATE FRANK, inside early, forced issue between horses after a half, dueled inside final turn, headed late turn, stayed close to mid stretch, gave best before tiring.
